alvarionVirtualApMIB.name: alvarionVirtualApMIB
alvarionVirtualApMIB.contactinfo: Alvarion Ltd. Postal: 21a HaBarzel St. P.O. Box 13139 Tel-Aviv 69710 Israel Phone: +972 3 645 6262

coVirtualAccessPointConfigTable.name: coVirtualAccessPointConfigTable
coVirtualAccessPointConfigTable.description: VSC configuration attributes. In tabular form to allow for multiple instances.

coVirtualAccessPointConfigEntry.name: coVirtualAccessPointConfigEntry
coVirtualAccessPointConfigEntry.description: An entry in the coVirtualAccessPointConfigTable. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex. coVirtualWlanProfileIndex - Uniquely access a profile for this particular 802.11 interface.

coVirtualApWlanProfileIndex.name: coVirtualApWlanProfileIndex
coVirtualApWlanProfileIndex.description: Specifies the index of the VSC profile.

coVirtualApSSID.name: coVirtualApSSID
coVirtualApSSID.description: Service Set ID assigned to the VSC. This value must be unique per radio interface.

coVirtualApBroadcastSSID.name: coVirtualApBroadcastSSID
coVirtualApBroadcastSSID.description: Specifies if the SSID is included in beacon frames. On Intersil hardware, only the first profile is manageable. Reading this attribute shall always return 'false' for the other profiles. Writing into this attribute for the other profiles will return an error.

coVirtualApMaximumNumberOfUsers.name: coVirtualApMaximumNumberOfUsers
coVirtualApMaximumNumberOfUsers.description: Specifies the maximum number of concurrent users that this profile can accept.

coVirtualApDefaultVLAN.name: coVirtualApDefaultVLAN
coVirtualApDefaultVLAN.description: Specifies the default VLAN to use for this profile when no radius authentication has taken place. The value 0 is used when no VLAN has been assigned to this profile. Writing to this object is only available on satellite devices.

coVirtualApAuthenMode.name: coVirtualApAuthenMode
coVirtualApAuthenMode.description: Specifies if user authentication is performed locally or via an AAA server.

coVirtualApAuthenProfileIndex.name: coVirtualApAuthenProfileIndex
coVirtualApAuthenProfileIndex.description: Specifies the AAA server profile to use for user authentication. This parameter only applies when the coVirtualApSecurity is set to 'wpa' or 'ieee802dot1x' or 'ieee802dot1xWithWep' and the coVirtualApAuthenMode set to 'profile' or 'localAndProfile'. When set to Zero, no AAA server profile is selected or on a public satellite device it could represent a pre-configured AAA profile.

coVirtualApUserAccountingEnabled.name: coVirtualApUserAccountingEnabled
coVirtualApUserAccountingEnabled.description: Indicates if accounting information is generated by the device and sent to the AAA server for users connecting to this profile. Accounting information will be generated only if a valid AAA server profile is configured for the coVirtualApAccountingProfileIndex attribute.

coVirtualApUserAccountingProfileIndex.name: coVirtualApUserAccountingProfileIndex
coVirtualApUserAccountingProfileIndex.description: Identifies the AAA server profile to be used for accounting information. The special value Zero indicates that no accounting profile is selected.

coVirtualApDefaultUserRateLimitationEnab.name: coVirtualApDefaultUserRateLimitationEnabled
coVirtualApDefaultUserRateLimitationEnab.description: Indicates if the default user rate limitation is enabled.

coVirtualApDefaultUserMaxTransmitRate.name: coVirtualApDefaultUserMaxTransmitRate
coVirtualApDefaultUserMaxTransmitRate.description: Identifies the default user maximum transmit rate.

coVirtualApDefaultUserMaxReceiveRate.name: coVirtualApDefaultUserMaxReceiveRate
coVirtualApDefaultUserMaxReceiveRate.description: Identifies the default user maximum receive rate.

coVirtualApDefaultUserBandwidthLevel.name: coVirtualApDefaultUserBandwidthLevel
coVirtualApDefaultUserBandwidthLevel.description: Identifies the default user bandwidth level.

coVirtualApOperState.name: coVirtualApOperState
coVirtualApOperState.description: Activate/Deactivate the Virtual Service Community in the radio.

alvarionVirtualApMIBCompliance.name: alvarionVirtualApMIBCompliance
alvarionVirtualApMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the Virtual Access Point MIB.

alvarionVirtualApMIBGroup.name: alvarionVirtualApMIBGroup
alvarionVirtualApMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects for use with Virtual Access Points.
